#14515
zaivrag carve_meat~
zaivrag~
The zaivrag stalks toward you slowly, emitting a low growl deep from its throat.
~
   Wiry golden fur broken by thick auburn stripes covers this creatures lithe
body.  Muscles ripple with its powerful movement about the exhibit.  The
zaivrag's enormous jaws jut out from its face revealing incisors almost the
same size of its head.  Its dark amber eyes peer out suspiciously and the wiry
fur becomes longer between its large pointy ears.  This longer, wiry fur is
darker at the crown of its head and goes all the way to the tip of its tail.
The creature's tail has a bulbous end with rows of spiny barbs that are ivory
at the base and become black at their sharp tips.  
~
