strength.  The slug's skin itself is wet, slimy brown that gives off a slight
neon-green glow similar to that emitted by phytoplankton in the ocean.  The
slug's eyes almost appear to be made of polished obsidian on flexible stalks
and the mouth below them hold razor sharp teeth that look like they could
shred diamonds.  
~
